{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cc339474-e526-46da-a1a0-f41c54cf0356","content":"No existing files found. Since this is a guidance request rather than an existing codebase, here's how to convert your page:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to enable compiled bindings\n\nIn your `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the namespace for your ViewModel and set `x:DataType` on the `ContentPage`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font Size: {0}'}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` — this tells the XAML compiler to resolve all `{Binding ...}` expressions against `SettingsViewModel` **at compile time**.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nOnce `x:DataType` is set, misspelled or missing properties (e.g., `{Binding Thme}`) become **compiler errors**, not silent runtime failures.\n\nTo ensure this is enforced strictly, add to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treat XAML binding warnings as errors -->\n    <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the diagnostic for unresolved compiled binding paths. Promoting it to an error guarantees your CI build fails on any binding typo.\n\n### 3. Opting out locally (when needed)\n\nIf a section uses a different runtime `BindingContext` (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate`), set a local `x:DataType`:\n\n```xml\n<DataTemplate x:DataType=\"model:SomeItem\">\n    <Label Text=\"{Binding Name}\" />\n</DataTemplate>\n```\n\nOr disable compiled bindings for one expression with `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"`.\n\n### Summary\n\n| What | How |\n|---|---|\n| Enable compiled bindings | `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the page |\n| Catch errors at build time | Automatic — typos become compiler errors |\n| Make warnings fatal in CI | `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>` |\n| Opt out locally | `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"` or set a different type |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3502b645-a952-45d8-a10d-f29c7af3cf19","outputTokens":697,"requestId":"F406:CA693:1E418C3:220E4DD:69E819AD"},"id":"c3f65efc-46d1-41a5-9710-6bc205dae406","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:43:39.757Z","parentId":"39b10e2c-5065-4a86-8dcc-26ffca360b2c"}
